wiki_overview.content:
<blog>

# Hutch-Pulse: Network Connectivity Maintenance Application

## Project Introduction

Hutch-Pulse is a sophisticated desktop application designed to maintain network connectivity for users of Hutch.lk internet services. Built with modern web technologies and Rust backend, it provides an elegant solution for automatically sending periodic authentication requests to keep internet connections alive without manual intervention.

### Purpose Statement
The application addresses the common issue of automatic disconnection in captive portal networks by implementing a background service that periodically sends authentication requests to maintain active sessions.

### Core Goals and Objectives
- **Automatic Connection Maintenance**: Periodically send authentication requests to prevent session timeouts
- **Minimal System Impact**: Operate as a lightweight tray application with minimal resource consumption
- **Cross-Platform Compatibility**: Support Windows desktop environments with native system integration
- **User-Friendly Interface**: Provide intuitive controls for starting, stopping, and monitoring the service

### Target Audience
- Users of Hutch.lk internet services experiencing frequent disconnections
- Environmentally conscious users seeking efficient connection management solutions
- Users requiring reliable internet connectivity for work or entertainment

## Technical Architecture

The application follows a hybrid architecture combining React frontend with Rust backend through Tauri, creating a native desktop experience with modern web development practices.

```mermaid
graph TD
    A[React Frontend] --> B[Tauri Bridge]
    B --> C[Rust Backend]
    C --> D[HTTP Client]
    C --> E[Windows API]
    C --> F[Tray Icon]
    D --> G[Hutch.lk Authentication Server]
    E --> H[Network Detection]
    F --> I[User Interaction]
    
    J[State Management] --> A
    K[Configuration] --> C
    L[Logging System] --> C
```

### Component Breakdown

**Frontend Layer (React)**
- Modern React application with TypeScript for type safety
- Radix UI components for accessible and consistent user interface
- Tailwind CSS for styling with custom design system
- React Router for page navigation
- React Query for state management and caching

**Backend Layer (Rust/Tauri)**
- Native Rust application leveraging Tauri framework
- Async runtime with Tokio for concurrent operations
- HTTP client for authentication requests
- Windows-specific network detection APIs
- System tray integration for desktop presence

**Integration Layer**
- Tauri bridge enabling seamless communication between frontend and backend
- Command handlers for bidirectional data exchange
- State synchronization mechanism

### Design Patterns

**State Machine Pattern**: The backend implements a finite state machine for service lifecycle management with clear transitions between STARTING, RUNNING, STOPPING, and STOPPED states.

**Observer Pattern**: The frontend subscribes to backend state changes through polling mechanisms, ensuring real-time updates without complex event handling.

**Factory Pattern**: Network detection logic adapts to different operating systems while maintaining consistent interfaces.

## Key Implementation

### Main Entry Points

**Frontend Entry Point**
- [`src/main.tsx`](src/main.tsx) - React application bootstrap with context providers
- [`src/App.tsx`](src/App.tsx) - Root component with routing and global providers

**Backend Entry Point**
- [`src-tauri/src/main.rs`](src-tauri/src/main.rs) - Tauri application entry point
- [`src-tauri/src/lib.rs`](src-tauri/src/lib.rs) - Core application logic and state management

### Core Modules

**Service State Management**
- [`src/hooks/useServiceState.ts`](src/hooks/useServiceState.ts) - Custom hook managing application state and backend communication

**UI Components**
- [`src/components/PrimaryControls.tsx`](src/components/PrimaryControls.tsx) - Main control panel with start/stop functionality
- [`src/components/StatusCard.tsx`](src/components/StatusCard.tsx) - Real-time status display
- [`src/components/AdvancedSettings.tsx`](src/components/AdvancedSettings.tsx) - Configuration options

**Backend Service Logic**
- [`src-tauri/src/lib.rs`](src-tauri/src/lib.rs) - Complete service implementation including network detection, authentication, and state management

### Configuration Approach

**Frontend Configuration**
- [`vite.config.ts`](vite.config.ts) - Vite build configuration with React plugin and path aliases
- [`tailwind.config.ts`](tailwind.config.ts) - Tailwind CSS configuration with custom design tokens
- [`tsconfig.json`](tsconfig.json) - TypeScript compilation settings

**Backend Configuration**
- [`src-tauri/Cargo.toml`](src-tauri/Cargo.toml) - Rust crate dependencies and build configuration
- [`src-tauri/tauri.conf.json`](src-tauri/tauri.conf.json) - Tauri application configuration including window properties and bundling settings

### External Dependencies

**Frontend Dependencies**
- React ecosystem with modern hooks and functional components
- Radix UI for accessible component primitives
- Recharts for data visualization
- React Query for state management
- Lucide React for consistent iconography

**Backend Dependencies**
- Tauri framework for desktop application creation
- Reqwest for HTTP client functionality
- Tokio async runtime for concurrent operations
- Serde for serialization/deserialization

### Integration Points

**Tauri Bridge Communication**
```mermaid
sequenceDiagram
    participant UI as React UI
    participant Bridge as Tauri Bridge
    participant Backend as Rust Backend
    
    UI->>+Bridge: invoke("get_status")
    Bridge->>+Backend: get_status()
    Backend-->>-Bridge: ServiceSnapshot
    Bridge-->>-UI: Snapshot Data
    
    UI->>+Bridge: invoke("start_service")
    Bridge->>+Backend: start_service()
    Backend->>Backend: Worker Loop
    Backend-->>-Bridge: Updated Snapshot
    Bridge-->>-UI: Service Started
```

**System Integration**
- Windows tray icon integration for desktop presence
- Network adapter detection using Windows-specific APIs
- Notification system for user feedback
- Auto-start functionality through system integration

## Key Features

### Functionality Overview

**Automatic Connection Maintenance**
- Periodic authentication requests to prevent session timeouts
- Intelligent network detection to adapt to connection changes
- Configurable intervals (20s to 5 minutes) for different network requirements

**User Interface Features**
- Minimal tray application with floating window
- Real-time status indicators for WiFi and internet connectivity
- Comprehensive logging system for troubleshooting
- Responsive controls for service management

**System Integration**
- Native Windows integration with tray icon and notifications
- Background operation without user interaction
- Automatic startup with system login
- Cross-platform compatibility considerations

### Implementation Highlights

**State Management Architecture**
- [`src/hooks/useServiceState.ts`](src/hooks/useServiceState.ts) - Centralized state management with polling mechanism
- [`src-tauri/src/lib.rs`](src-tauri/src/lib.rs) - Thread-safe state with mutex protection

**Network Detection System**
- [`src-tauri/src/lib.rs`](src-tauri/src/lib.rs) - Windows-specific network adapter detection
- Real-time connectivity monitoring with automatic service suspension

**User Experience Design**
- [`src/components/PrimaryControls.tsx`](src/components/PrimaryControls.tsx) - Intuitive control interface with visual feedback
- [`src/components/StatusCard.tsx`](src/components/StatusCard.tsx) - Clear status visualization

### Feature Architecture

```mermaid
stateDiagram-v2
    [*] --> Stopped
    Stopped --> Starting: Start Service
    Starting --> Running: Network OK
    Starting --> Stopped: Start Failed
    Running --> Stopping: Stop Service
    Stopping --> Stopped: Service Stopped
    Running --> Stopped: Network Lost
    Stopped --> Error: Unexpected Failure
    Error --> Stopped: Recovery
    
    state Starting {
        [*] --> CheckingNetwork
        CheckingNetwork --> CheckingInternet
        CheckingInternet --> [*]
    }
```

**Service Lifecycle Management**
- Automated state transitions based on network conditions
- Graceful error handling with user notifications
- Persistent logging for debugging and monitoring

**Performance Optimization**
- Efficient polling mechanism with configurable intervals
- Memory management with log rotation
- Minimal CPU and memory footprint during idle periods

---

**Sources:**
- [package.json](package.json)
- [Cargo.toml](src-tauri/Cargo.toml)
- [tauri.conf.json](src-tauri/tauri.conf.json)
- [main.tsx](src/main.tsx)
- [App.tsx](src/App.tsx)
- [Index.tsx](src/pages/Index.tsx)
- [useServiceState.ts](src/hooks/useServiceState.ts)
- [lib.rs](src-tauri/src/lib.rs)
- [main.rs](src-tauri/src/main.rs)
- [PrimaryControls.tsx](src/components/PrimaryControls.tsx)
- [tailwind.config.ts](tailwind.config.ts)
- [vite.config.ts](vite.config.ts)

</blog>
